boundary in either direction.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Call/SMS</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>84a780e4-1782-4f47-89c6-4a7784d26a91</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>D4</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>D384a780e4-1782-4f47-89c6-4a7784d26a916e015ab5-3b2b-4779-98c0-85706d3b52d06fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>6e015ab5-3b2b-4779-98c0-85706d3b52d0</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>462</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>84a780e4-1782-4f47-89c6-4a7784d26a91:6e015ab5-3b2b-4779-98c0-85706d3b52d0:6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Potential Process Crash or Stop for TCU</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Denial Of Service</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Denial of Service happens when the process or a datastore is not able to service incoming requests or perform up to spec.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>TCU crashes, halts, stops or runs slowly; in all cases violating an availability metric.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Call/SMS</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>84a780e4-1782-4f47-89c6-4a7784d26a91</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>D3</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>I684a780e4-1782-4f47-89c6-4a7784d26a916e015ab5-3b2b-4779-98c0-85706d3b52d06fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>6e015ab5-3b2b-4779-98c0-85706d3b52d0</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>461</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>84a780e4-1782-4f47-89c6-4a7784d26a91:6e015ab5-3b2b-4779-98c0-85706d3b52d0:6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Flow Sniffing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Information Disclosure</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Information disclosure happens when the information can be read by an unauthorized party.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Data flowing across Call/SMS may be sniffed by an attacker. Depending on what type of data an attacker can read, it may be used to attack other parts of the system or simply be a disclosure of information leading to compliance violations. Consider encrypting the data flow.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Call/SMS</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>84a780e4-1782-4f47-89c6-4a7784d26a91</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>I6</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>E5c1b190e2-91fb-4c5b-878e-220c0ca15aeb2754efb1-4059-41d2-9adc-7ba862a2d6013fa9915a-486c-4d3d-b246-1d38c2f6e586</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>2754efb1-4059-41d2-9adc-7ba862a2d601</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>153</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>c1b190e2-91fb-4c5b-878e-220c0ca15aeb:2754efb1-4059-41d2-9adc-7ba862a2d601:3fa9915a-486c-4d3d-b246-1d38c2f6e586</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Elevation Using Impersonation</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Elevation Of Privilege</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>A user subject gains increased capability or privilege by taking advantage of an implementation bug.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Gateway may be able to impersonate the context of Chassis Control Module (CCM) in order to gain additional privilege.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>C-CAN data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>c1b190e2-91fb-4c5b-878e-220c0ca15aeb</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>3fa9915a-486c-4d3d-b246-1d38c2f6e586</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>E5</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>E5dd03bf0c-89d6-423a-84bb-18753c23b416a21422fc-7dd5-4cb4-89c7-4f1b9b007fcaa8820ccf-1189-4a07-9f83-eff024c2f212</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>a21422fc-7dd5-4cb4-89c7-4f1b9b007fca</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>259</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>dd03bf0c-89d6-423a-84bb-18753c23b416:a21422fc-7dd5-4cb4-89c7-4f1b9b007fca:a8820ccf-1189-4a07-9f83-eff024c2f212</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Elevation Using Impersonation</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Elevation Of Privilege</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>A user subject gains increased capability or privilege by taking advantage of an implementation bug.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Door may be able to impersonate the context of Body Control Module (BCM) in order to gain additional privilege.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Lock / Unlock operation</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>dd03bf0c-89d6-423a-84bb-18753c23b416</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>a8820ccf-1189-4a07-9f83-eff024c2f212</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>E5</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>E5670d5323-d14d-4836-901d-de9aa20d843589fcc53c-e868-4637-802f-a936968ed469ec2e0748-6003-4779-b7fc-4785e92cc56f</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>89fcc53c-e868-4637-802f-a936968ed469</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>398</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>670d5323-d14d-4836-901d-de9aa20d8435:89fcc53c-e868-4637-802f-a936968ed469:ec2e0748-6003-4779-b7fc-4785e92cc56f</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Elevation Using Impersonatio