iority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing the Automatic Transmission (AT) System External Entity</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing is when a process or entity is something other than its claimed identity. Examples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Automatic Transmission (AT) System may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to unauthorized access to Transmission Control Module(TCM). Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the external entity.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Transmission Status</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>670d5323-d14d-4836-901d-de9aa20d8435</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>ec2e0748-6003-4779-b7fc-4785e92cc56f</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>S3</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>E5facdf548-7286-4407-8652-83e9ab0c66496a366c00-1f40-41ad-9fb9-66927976e9c5847a84fd-0f08-4887-b15d-d120566cb9d1</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>6a366c00-1f40-41ad-9