mples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>TCU may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to information disclosure by Smart Phone. Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the destination process.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Call/SMS</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>84a780e4-1782-4f47-89c6-4a7784d26a91</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>S2</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>S2d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6932dacbe-a48f-4038-a846-1d9b317f0e676fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>932dacbe-a48f-4038-a846-1d9b317f0e67</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>425</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6:932dacbe-a48f-4038-a846-1d9b317f0e67:6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing the TCU Process</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing is when a process or entity is something other than its claimed identity. Examples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>TCU may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to information disclosure by Telematics Server. Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the destination process.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Telematic data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>S2</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>D56fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>424</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de:1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654:d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Store Inaccessible</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Denial Of Service</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Denial of Service happens when the process or a datastore is not able to service incoming requests or perform up to spec.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>An external agent prevents access to a data store on the other side of the trust boundary.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Telematics data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>D5</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>D46fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>423</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de:1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654:d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Flow Telematics data Is Potentially Interrupted</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Denial Of Service</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Denial of Service happens when the process or a datastore is not able to service incoming requests or perform up to spec.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>An external agent interrupts data flowing across a trust boundary in either direction.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Telematics data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>D4</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>I66fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>422</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de:1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654:d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Flow Sniffing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Information Disclosure</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Information disclosure happens when the information can be read by an unauthorized party.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Data flowing across Telematics data may be sniffed by an attacker. Depending on what type of data an attacker can read, it may be used to attack other parts of the system or simply be a disclosure of information leading to compliance violations. Consider encrypting the data flow.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Telematics data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>I6</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>R86fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>421</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de:1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654:d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Store Denies Telematics Server Potentially Writing Data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Repudiation</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Repudiation threats involve an adversary denying that something happened.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Telematics Server claims that it did not write data received from an entity on the other side of the trust boundary. Consider using logging or auditing to record the source, time, and summary of the received data.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Telematics data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>R8</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>T186fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>420</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de:1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654:d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>The Telematics Server Data Store Could Be Corrupted</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering is the act of altering the bits. Tampering with a process involves changing bits in the running process. Similarly, Tampering with a data flow involves changing bits on the wire or between two running processes.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Data flowing across Telematics data may be tampered with by an attacker. This may lead to corruption of Telematics Server. Ensure the integrity of the data flow to the data store.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Telematics data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>T18</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>E53fa9915a-486c-4d3d-b246-1d38c2f6e586ed46525a-f21b-45f3-872b-ab9f9210c9bbaa0c3faa-10e3-4fe7-8906-ae9d50b8e198</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>ed46525a-f21b-45f3-872b-ab9f9210c9bb</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>400</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>3fa9915a-486c-4d3d-b246-1d38c2f6e586:ed46525a-f21b-45f3-872b-ab9f9210c9bb:aa0c3faa-10e3-4fe7-8906-ae9d50b8e198</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Elevation Using Impersonation</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Elevation Of Privilege</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>A user subject gains increased capability or privilege by taking advantage of an implementation bug.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Engine Control Module (ECM) may be able to impersonate the context of Gateway in order to gain additional privilege.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>RPM</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>3fa9915a-486c-4d3d-b246-1d38c2f6e586</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>aa0c3faa-10e3-4fe7-8906-ae9d50b8e198</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>E5</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>fals