rThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Information Disclosure</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Information disclosure happens when the information can be read by an unauthorized party.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Improper data protection of Telematics Server can allow an attacker to read information not intended for disclosure. Review authorization settings.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Telematic data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>I23</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>S7d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6932dacbe-a48f-4038-a846-1d9b317f0e676fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>932dacbe-a48f-4038-a846-1d9b317f0e67</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>405</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6:932dacbe-a48f-4038-a846-1d9b317f0e67:6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing of Source Data Store Telematics Server</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing is when a process or entity is something other than its claimed identity. Examples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Telematics Server may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to incorrect data delivered to TCU. Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the source data store.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Telematic data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>S7</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>D26fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>404</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de:1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654:d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Potential Excessive Resource Consumption for TCU or Telematics Server</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Denial Of Service</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Denial of Service happens when the process or a datastore is not able to service incoming requests or perform up to spec.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Does TCU or Telematics Server take explicit steps to control resource consumption? Resource consumption attacks can be hard to deal with, and there are times that it makes sense to let the OS do the job. Be careful that your resource requests don't deadlock, and that they do timeout.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Telematics data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>D2</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>S7.16fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f690894f-3312-48a6-bee3-04ce9b111ab4</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>403</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de:1dcea2bf-d905-47b6-acd4-afee35c9c654:d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing of Destination Data Store Telematics Server</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing is when a process or entity is something other than its claimed identity. Examples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Telematics Server may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to data being written to the attacker's target instead of Telematics Server. Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the destination data store.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Telematics data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>6fcd03b4-7101-49f4-8915-c1bb9349e6de</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>d0670c30-af48-41b5-97fa-74bd9e49efb6</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>S7.1</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide><